# Deep Chat styling

The bear chat UI uses the [Deep Chat](https://deepchat.dev) web component (`<deep-chat>`).

## Styling reference

Full docs: <https://deepchat.dev/docs/styles/>

Design examples (including "full width input"): <https://deepchat.dev/examples/design/>

## Key properties used in `bear_chat.html`

| JS property | What it controls |
|---|---|
| `style` / `chatStyle` | Host element (outer container) |
| `messageStyles` | Per-role bubble colours, alignment (`outerContainer.justifyContent`), padding |
| `textInput` | Input box styling, placeholder, character limit |
| `submitButtonStyles` | Send/loading/stop/disabled button states |
| `inputAreaStyle` | Bottom bar wrapping input + buttons |
| `auxiliaryStyle` | Raw CSS injected into Shadow DOM (scrollbar, internal overrides, **downwards grid row fix** so `#messages` does not clip `#input` after `loadHistory`) |
| `avatars` | Avatar images/visibility per role |
| `names` | Name labels per role (text, colour, font) |

## Conventions

- Page chrome and layout live in [`den/src/web/assets/css/specifics.css`](../../den/src/web/assets/css/specifics.css) under `html.den-bear-chat-page` (imported via `style.css`).
- Colours and spacing for the Deep Chat host and bubbles are driven by tokens in [`den/src/web/assets/css/style.css`](../../den/src/web/assets/css/style.css) (`--surface-color`, `--chat-*`, etc.). The host may use `var(--…)` in `chat.style`; `auxiliaryStyle` also prefers `var(--…)`. For `messageStyles` / `textInput` / `submitButtonStyles`, pass **computed** lengths from `resolveDeepChatLayoutTokens()` in `bear_chat.html` (batched light-DOM probe): `getPropertyValue` on `:root` for `calc(var(--spacing-unit)…)` tokens often returns the raw `calc`, which does not resolve inside Deep Chat’s Shadow DOM and can **collapse the text input**.
- No rounded corners (`borderRadius: '0'`) per the Den design system.
- User bubbles: right-aligned, page-colour background with thin border.
- AI bubbles: left-aligned, surface-colour background.
- Input uses the "full width input" pattern: `border: 'unset'`, `borderTop` separator, `width: '100%'`.
